SIMPLE: indecisive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indecisive
<hw>In`de*ci"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ind⟦eacute⟧cisif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not decisive; not bringing to a final or ultimate
issue; <as>as, an <ex>indecisive</ex> battle, argument,
answer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The campaign had everywhere been <qex>indecisive</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Undetermined; prone to indecision; irresolute;
unsettled; wavering; vacillating; hesitating; <as>as, an
<ex>indecisive</ex> state of mind; an <ex>indecisive</ex>
character.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indecisively</ent>⟦br⟧
